{"parse":{"title":"The Scarlet Professor","pageid":55685310,"revid":854519392,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:302px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Spofford_and_Arvin.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c3/Spofford_and_Arvin.jpg/300px-Spofford_and_Arvin.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"220\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c3/Spofford_and_Arvin.jpg/450px-Spofford_and_Arvin.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c3/Spofford_and_Arvin.jpg/600px-Spofford_and_Arvin.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"3856\" data-file-height=\"2832\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Spofford_and_Arvin.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Ned Spofford (William Hite) with Newton Arvin (Keith Phares) in a scene from <i>The Scarlet Professor</i></div></div></div> \n<p><i><b>The Scarlet Professor </b></i>is an <a href=\"/wiki/Opera\" title=\"Opera\">opera</a>  by the American composer <a href=\"/wiki/Eric_Sawyer\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Eric Sawyer\">Eric Sawyer</a> with <a href=\"/wiki/Libretto\" title=\"Libretto\">libretto</a> by Harley Erdman, based the biography<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> by <a href=\"/wiki/Barry_Werth\" title=\"Barry Werth\">Barry Werth</a>. \n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Performance_history\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Performance history</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Roles\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Roles</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Instrumentation\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Instrumentation</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Reception\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Reception</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#External_links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">6</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External links</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Performance_history\">Performance history</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=The_Scarlet_Professor&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Performance history\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The world premieres of the fully staged opera occurred on September 15\u201317, 2017, at <a href=\"/wiki/Smith_College\" title=\"Smith College\">Smith College</a> where the events that inspired the performance took place. The opera was performed without intermission with running time of about one hour and 40 minutes. A symposium<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> on the <a href=\"/wiki/Newton_Arvin\" title=\"Newton Arvin\">Arvin</a> case was held all day on September 16. The following weekend the opera was performed with a cast of young artists from the Five Colleges consortium of Western Massachusetts.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Roles\">Roles</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=The_Scarlet_Professor&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Roles\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<table class=\"wikitable\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<th>Role\n</th>\n<th><a href=\"/wiki/Voice_type\" title=\"Voice type\">Voice type</a>\n</th>\n<th>Premiere cast, 15 September 2017<br />Conductor: Eduardo Leandro\n</th></tr>\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Newton_Arvin\" title=\"Newton Arvin\">Newton Arvin</a></td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Tenor\" title=\"Tenor\">tenor</a></td>\n<td>William Hite\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Ned Spofford</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Baritone\" title=\"Baritone\">baritone</a></td>\n<td>Keith Phares\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Hester_Prynne\" title=\"Hester Prynne\">Hester Prynne</a></td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Mezzo-soprano\" title=\"Mezzo-soprano\">mezzo-soprano</a></td>\n<td>Blythe Gaissert\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Helen Bacon</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Soprano\" title=\"Soprano\">soprano</a></td>\n<td>Sarah Pelletier\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Truman_Capote\" title=\"Truman Capote\">Truman Capote</a></td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Countertenor\" title=\"Countertenor\">countertenor</a></td>\n<td>Bryan Pollock\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Officer Regan</td>\n<td>baritone</td>\n<td>James Dernier\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Doctor</td>\n<td>soprano</td>\n<td>Kristen Watson\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Arthur Summerfield</td>\n<td>baritone</td>\n<td>Sumner Thompson\n</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Instrumentation\">Instrumentation</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=The_Scarlet_Professor&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Instrumentation\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The 9-piece instrumental ensemble consisted of piano, percussion, flute, clarinet, tenor saxophone, and strings, with both electric and double bass.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Reception\">Reception</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=The_Scarlet_Professor&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: Reception\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Reviewer Marvin J. Ward found  the opera a \"compelling and captivating work\", adding \"...composer Eric Sawyer has a penchant for choosing historical events, especially local ones, as the subjects of his operas. This is the third that I have seen, each more polished and refined than its predecessor, with <i>The Scarlet Professor</i> scoring a 10/10 in my book.\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=The_Scarlet_Professor&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Werth, Barry. <i>The Scarlet Professor: <a href=\"/wiki/Newton_Arvin\" title=\"Newton Arvin\">Newton Arvin</a>: A Literary Life Shattered by Scandal.</i>. Random House, 2001.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.smith.edu/news/singing-the-story/\">\"Singing the Story\"</a>. <i>Grecourt Gate</i>. 2017-09-07<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2017-10-28</span></span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;